  ./COVERAGE.md:502:| `io.helidon.builder:helidon-builder-api` | [4.3.4<br>- 4.5.1-M1](metadata/io.helidon.builder/helidon-builder-api/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Helidon Builder API provides annotations and runtime APIs used to define blueprint interfaces for generated Helidon builder and prototype types. It is the compile-scope companion to the builder code generator, letting generated builders compile and run while keeping builder generation reflection-free.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/io.helidon.builder/helidon-builder-api/) |
  ./COVERAGE.md:503:| `io.helidon.common.features:helidon-common-features` | [4.3.4<br>- 4.5.1-M1](metadata/io.helidon.common.features/helidon-common-features/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Helidon Common Features discovers and reports the Helidon features available on an application's class path for a selected Helidon flavor. It builds a feature tree from Helidon feature metadata and logs invalid, preview, deprecated, incubating, and native-image support information.</details> | [100.0% (1/1 calls)](stats/io.helidon.common.features/helidon-common-features/) |
  ./COVERAGE.md:504:| `io.helidon.common.features:helidon-common-features-api` | [4.3.4<br>- 4.5.1-M1](metadata/io.helidon.common.features/helidon-common-features-api/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Helidon Common Features API provides source-retention annotations and supporting types for declaring Helidon feature metadata on Java modules. It lets Helidon components describe feature names, paths, flavors, preview/incubating status, and ahead-of-time/native-image support for generation into the feature registry.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/io.helidon.common.features/helidon-common-features-api/) |
  ./COVERAGE.md:505:| `io.helidon.common.features:helidon-common-features-metadata` | [4.3.4<br>- 4.5.1-M1](metadata/io.helidon.common.features/helidon-common-features-metadata/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Helidon Common Features Metadata provides model types and registry support for describing Helidon features and their metadata. It is shared by Helidon feature code generation and runtime components, including feature flavor, status, deprecation, and AOT metadata handling.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/io.helidon.common.features/helidon-common-features-metadata/) |
