 registry.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/io.helidon.common.features/helidon-common-features-api/) |\n./COVERAGE.md:505:| `io.helidon.common.features:helidon-common-features-metadata` | [4.3.4<br>- 4.5.1-M1](metadata/io.helidon.common.features/helidon-common-features-metadata/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Helidon Common Features Metadata provides model types and registry support for describing Helidon features and their metadata. It is shared by Helidon feature code generation and runtime components, including feature flavor, status, deprecation, and AOT metadata handling.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/io.helidon.common.features/helidon-common-features-metadata/) |\n./COVERAGE.md:506:| `io.helidon.common:helidon-common` | [4.3.4<br>- 4.5.1-M1](metadata/io.helidon.common/helidon-common/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Helidon Common provides shared utility APIs for Helidon projects, including builders, error collection, lazy values, weighted services, generic type helpers, size parsing, and Native Image support helpers. It supplies reusable Java infrastructure used across Helidon microservice libraries and applications.</details> | [100.0% (1/1 calls)](stats/io.helidon.common/helidon-common/) |\n./COVERAGE.md:507:| `io.helidon.common:helidon-common-buffers` | [4.3.4<br>- 4.5.1-M1](metadata/io.helidon.common/helidon-common-buffers/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Helidon Common Buffers provides byte-buffer abstractions and byte operation utilities used by Helidon components. It includes fixed, growing, composite, and read-only buffer data implementations along with readers, writers, ASCII helpers, and lazy string handling.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/io.helidon.common/helidon-common-buffers/) |\n./COVERAGE.md:508:| `io.helidon.common:helidon-common-config` | [4.3.4<br>- 4.5.1-M1](metadata/io.helidon.common/helidon-common-config/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Helidon Common Config provides immutable tree-structured configuration abstractions and values used by Helidon common components. It lets JVM code create or obtain configuration from providers, navigate keys and nodes, map values, and integrate configured services.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/io.helidon.common/helidon-common-config/) |\n./COVERAGE.md:509:| `io.helidon.common:helidon-common-configurable` | [4.3.4<br>- 4.5.1-M1](metadata/io.helidon.common/helidon-common-configurable/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Helidon Common Configurable provides Java utilities that can be configured through Helidon common configuration, including thread pools, resources, allow lists, and cache helpers. It is a core Helidon support module used by other Helidon components to construct configurable runtime resources.</details> | [100.0% (1/1 calls)](stats/io.helidon.common/helidon-common-configurable/) |\n./COVERAGE.md:510:| `io.helidon.common:helidon-common-context` | [4.3.4<br>- 4.5.1-M1](metadata/io.helidon.common/helidon-common-context/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Helidon Common Context provides a registry for contextual objects scoped to Helidon components such as servers and requests, with type and classifier-based lookup. It also propagates the current context across thread boundaries and wrapped executor services.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/io.helidon.common/helidon-common-context/) |\n./COVERAGE.md:511:| `io.helidon.common:helidon-common-mapper` | [4.3.4<br>- 4.5.1-M1](metadata/io.helidon.common/helidon-common-mapper/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Helidon Common Mapper provides a generic mapping facility for converting values between Java types. It includes mapper and resolver APIs plus service-provider integration used by Helidon's configuration and common modules.</details> | [100.0% (1/1 calls)](stats/io.helidon.common/helidon-common-mapper/) |\n./COVERAGE.md:512:| `io.helidon.common:helidon-common-media-type` | [4.3.4<br>- 4.5.1-M1](metadata/io.helidon.common/helidon-common-media-type/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Helidon Common Media Type provides Java utilities for representing, parsing, and detecting media types. It maps resources such as files, URIs, and URLs to media types for Helidon and HTTP-related code.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/io.helidon.common/helidon-common-media-type/) |\n./COVERAGE.md:513:| `io.helidon.common:helidon-common-types` | [4.3.4<br>- 4.5.1-M1](metadata/io.helidon.common/helidon-common-types/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Helidon Common Types provides abstractions for Java language types that can be used during annotation processing and at runtime without relying on reflection. It models type, element, annotation, module, and signature metadata used by Helidon common and builder infrastructure.</details> | [100.0% (1/1 calls)](stats/io.helidon.common/helidon-common-types/) |\n./COVERAGE.md:514:| `io.helidon.config:helidon-config` | [4.3.4<br>- 4.5.1-M1](metadata/io.helidon.config/helidon-config/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Helidon Config is the core configuration module for Helidon applications. It loads, merges, maps, and monitors application configuration from sources such as files, classpath resources, URLs, system properties, environment variables, and in-memory maps.</details> | [100.0% (9/9 calls)](stats/io.helidon.config/helidon-config/) |\n./COVERAGE.md:515:| `io.helidon.integrations.graal:helidon-graal-native-image-extension` | [4.3.4<br>- 4.5.1-M1](metadata/io.helidon.integrations.graal/helidon-graal-native-image-extension/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Helidon Graal Native Image Extension contributes GraalVM native-image feature registration and configuration for Helidon applications. It scans Helidon, CDI, Jersey, service descriptor, and @Reflected usage at image build time to register required reflection, resources, and build-time initialization.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/io.helidon.integrations.graal/helidon-graal-native-image-extension/) |\n./COVERAGE.md:516:| `io.helidon.logging:helidon-logging-common` | [4.3.4<br>- 4.5.1-M1](metadata/io.helidon.logging/helidon-logging-common/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Helidon Logging Common provides shared logging infrastructure for Helidon, including MDC propagation and SPI hooks for logging providers. It also supports logging initialization during native-image build time and runtime.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/io.helidon.logging/helidon-logging-common/) |\n./COVERAGE.md:517:| `io.helidon.logging:helidon-logging-jul` | [4.3.4<br>- 4.5.1-M1](metadata/io.helidon.logging/helidon-logging-jul/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Helidon Logging JUL integrates Helidon logging with Java Util Logging, including formatters, a console handler, and service providers for logging and MDC support. It lets Helidon applications use JUL while propagating mapped diagnostic context through Helidon common context.</details> | [100.0% (2/2 calls)](stats/io.helidon.logging/helidon-logging-jul/) |\n./COVERAGE.md:518:| `io.helidon.metadata:helidon-metadata` | [4.3.4<br>- 4.5.1-M1](metadata/io.helidon.metadata/helidon-metadata/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Helidon Metadata provides APIs for discovering Helidon metadata files and listing metadata resources by file name. It can use merged manifests, classpath resources, or classpath and module path scanning so Helidon components can locate generated metadata at runtime.</details> | [100.0% (2/2 calls)](stats/io.helidon.metadata/helidon-metadata/) |\n./COVERAGE.md:519:| `io.helidon.metadata:helidon-metadata-hson` | [4.3.4<br>- 4.5.1-M1](metadata/io.helidon.metadata/helidon-metadata-hson/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Helidon Metadata HSON provides a tiny parser, writer, and object model for Helidon's simplified JSON metadata format. It is intended for Helidon annotation processor